description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Health, Safety &amp; Security Team to work with and support the Team in providing professional, timely and comprehensive advice and guidance to ensure the health, safety and security of staff, service users, property, equipment and materials to enable the trust to provide the best possible duty of care to its service users and staff&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Health, Safety &amp; Security Team work within the Estates and Facilities Management Directorate across the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main duties and responsibilities will include assisting with and producing, reviewing and monitoring compliance with Trust policies relating to health and safety issues, investigate and produce reports on RIDDOR incidents and participate in serious untoward incidents where identified. Assist in developing the health and safety training presentations and deliver across the trust in line with mandatory training programme. Assist with further development of the Health, Safety &amp; Security Management system, conduct audits and analysis of results. Conduct assessments when required for DSE, return to work, workplace, new and expectant mothers, lone working or where identified by a service that assistance with assessment is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is expected that the post holder will have either a NEBOSH Certificate in Health &amp; Safety. Minimum requirement would be the Level 4 or Vocational Qualification for Occupational Health and Safety Practice with at least 2 years experience of working in health and safety. Knowledge of NHS is desirable. Although the main office base is at Durham d&lt;span&gt;ue to the nature of the role it is essential that applicants are able to travel independently across the locality and have access to a suitable vehicle for business purposes. If necessary, adjustments can be considered in accordance with the Equality Act 2010.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHelen CunninghamJob titleHealth &amp; Safety ManagerEmail addressh.cunningham1@nhs.netTelephone number07787128927Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Cunningham, Health &amp; Safety Manager on 077871 28927.&lt;/p&gt;
